Geocache Description:

The cache is NOT located at the above coordinates! The location of the cache must be found by solving the mystery... once solved the coordinates will become clear and will then be accessable by most anyone. Wheelchair access may be slightly difficult. Bring small items for trade. THIS CACHE IS IN A HIGH FOOT TRAFFIC AREA...BE VERY DISCRETE! ALTHOUGH AVAILAVLE AT ALL TIMES, AN EVENING VISIT IS RECOMENDED FOR THE INTEGRITY OF THE CACHE LOCATION.

This mystery starts as all good mysteries do...with a precarious case of murder...only to be solved by Sherlock Holmes and his trusty assistant Watson.

Holmes-"Watson! I do believe I have almost solved the clues left behind by 'The Murderer'!!"
Watson-"Do tell Holmes!!"
Holmes-"Of course my dear Watson, but first I must solve the last part of the riddle...fetch the constable and bring him to my office...I have all of my notes in there..."
Watson-"Right'O, back in a jiffy" >
>

--Watson returns with the constable back in to Holmes' office to find him deceased on the floor with the side window broken out, the murderer no where in sight. There on the floor...by Holmes' lifeless body, lies his notes and a message written with his own blood...

The message is as follows: "It’s elementary my dear Watson"

While rummaging through Holmes' notes he finds the final piece of evidence that Holmes' didn't have time to decrypt. On the paper is scribbled the following:


&# 71 ; &# 101 ; &# 65 ; &# 108 ;&# 67 ;& # 109;& #7 2; & #1 01;

&# 68;&# 1 15 ;& #7 6;& # 97 ;& # 82;& #98 ;& # 78;

That is it...the key to finding your dear friend and colleague's killer. It’s all up to you now Watson...decrypt this evidence and capture "The Murderer"
